[[File:Budapest Airport A Porta (Gate A).JPG|thumb|Gate A at [[Budapest Airport]] leads to the former CAA-HU head office]] The '''Civil Aviation Authority''' ('''CAA-HU''', {{lang-hu|'''Polgári Légiközlekedési Hatóság'''}}, '''PLH'''), earlier the '''Civil Aviation Administration''' ('''Légügyi Igazgatóság''', '''LUI'''), was a government agency of [[Hungary]] that acted as that country's civil aviation authority. The head office was located in Building 13 of [[Budapest Ferenc Liszt International Airport|Budapest Ferihegy International Airport]] Terminal 1 in [[Budapest]].<ref>"[https://web.archive.org/web/20050301072453/http://www.caa.hu/plh/elerhetosegunk.htm Elérhetőségünk]." Civil Aviation Authority. 1 March 2005. Retrieved on 20 February 2012. "Cím: Budapest, Ferihegy I., 13-as épület. Megközelíthető: Ferihegy I. "A" porta Levélcím: 1675 Budapest, PF 41."</ref>
In 2007 the successor agency, the [[National Transport Authority (Hungary)|National Transport Authority]], began operations on 1 January 2007.<ref>"[http://old.nkh.gov.hu/en/ Home] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120307120627/http://old.nkh.gov.hu/en/ |date=2012-03-07 }}." [[National Transport Authority (Hungary)|National Transport Authority]]. Retrieved on 20 February 2012.</ref> The [[Transportation Safety Bureau]] (previously the [[Civil Aviation Safety Bureau of Hungary]]) is the agency that investigates transport accidents and incidents.
