{{Infobox political party |country = Andorra |name = Democratic Renewal |native_name = Renovació Democràtica |colorcode = orange |logo = |leader = Ricard de Haro |foundation = 2005 |ideology = [[Social liberalism]] |position = [[Centre-left politics|Centre-left]] |headquarters = [[Andorra la Vella]] |colours = Green, Black, Orange, White |members = |european = ''None'' |international = ''None'' |website = }}
'''Democratic Renewal''' ({{lang-ca|Renovació Democràtica}}, RD) is a social-liberal [[political party]] in [[Andorra]].
==History== For the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2005|2005 parliamentary elections]] the party was part of an alliance with the [[Social Democratic Party (Andorra)|Social Democratic Party]] and [[Parochial Union of Independents Group]] named '''L'Alternativa'''.<ref name=NS>[[Dieter Nohlen|Nohlen D]] & Stöver P (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p164 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> The alliance won twelve seats.
The party did not contest the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2009|2009 elections]], but instead supported [[Andorra for Change]], which won three seats.<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/arc/2005_09.htm Elections in 2009] IPU</ref> It did not participate in the [[Andorran parliamentary election, 2011|2011 elections]].<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/2005_E.htm Latest elections] IPU</ref>
