'''Dibër Street''' ({{lang-sq|Rruga e Dibrës}}, formerly ''Rruga Bajram Curri'') is a major street in [[Tirana]], [[Albania]]. It runs northeast from the central [[Skanderbeg Square]], just south of the [[Tirana International Hotel]]. The Mother Teresa Hospital ([[QSUT]]) is located on this street.<ref>Jeroen van Marle, Alwyn Thomson, ''Tirana In Your Pocket'', p.20</ref>

