It was formed in 1902, and reorganized in 1904 into [[Upper Senegal and Niger]].
==Stamps== {{Main|Postage stamps and postal history of Senegambia and Niger}} Despite its brief existence, the French government still managed to issue [[postage stamp]]s for the administrative unit, in the form of a version of its [[Navigation and Commerce|Navigation and Commerce series]], inscribed "SENEGAMBIE / ET NIGER".
