'''Shkumbin''' is an [[Albanians|Albanian]] [[given name]] for males.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aboutnames.ch/albanian.htm#gnShkumbin|title=Albanian names|accessdate=6 November 2010|publisher=aboutnames.ch}}</ref> It derives from [[Shkumbin]], a [[river]] in central [[Albania]], flowing into the [[Adriatic Sea]], which is considered the dividing line for the two dialects of the [[Albanian language]]: [[Tosk Albanian|Tosk]] (to the south) and [[Gheg Albanian|Gheg]] (to the north).

Notable people bearing this name include:
* [[Shkumbin Arsllani]], Albanian footballer from [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]]

